subsection.para:
The final result is the following formula for the rating difference:&linebreak;R = a2(N)*EPM+b(N)*EPC,&linebreak;
where&linebreak;a2(N) = 8798 + 25526/N,&linebreak;
and&linebreak;b(N) = 863 - 519/N.

The linear fit of N*a(N) gives the following rating
formula:&linebreak;R = (11971 + 23681/N) * DEPD. &linebreak; In the figure
below the formula is plotted along with the actual data points;

The bilinear fit improves the linear fit especially for
large cube errors. Usually the linear estimate is too high, reflecting too much
weight given to the cube errors, for which the bilinear formula corrects. The
data is well approximated by&linebreak;R = a2(N)*EPM+b(N)*EPC,&linebreak;
where&linebreak;a2(N) = 8798 + 25526/N,&linebreak;
and&linebreak;b(N) = 863 - 519/N.
